## Task
Fetch billing data: contact plan properties + subscription plans catalog from HubDB.

## File: `src/data-queries/billing.graphql`

```graphql
# label: "Portal Billing"
# description: "Current plan + plan catalog"
# $contact_id: {{ request.contact.contact_vid || '' }}
query billing($contact_id: String!) {
  CRM {
    contact(uniqueIdentifier: "id", uniqueIdentifierValue: $contact_id) {
      current_plan
      plan_price
      billing_interval
      period_start
      period_end
      plan_status
    }
  }
  HUBDB {
    subscription_plans_collection(filter: { is_active__eq: true }, orderBy: "display_order") {
      items {
        name
        description
        price
        currency
        interval
        systems_per_year
        features
        display_order
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Steps
- [ ] Create .graphql file
- [ ] Test in GraphiQL — verify both CRM and HUBDB data return in one query

## Depends On
- #11 Contact properties
- #12 HubDB subscription_plans table

## Task
Write the query for a single order detail page, using dynamic slug from URL.

## File: `src/data-queries/order_detail.graphql`

```graphql
# label: "Order Detail"
# description: "Single order detail with status history"
# $order_number: {{ request.path_param_dict.dynamic_slug }}
# $contact_id: {{ request.contact.contact_vid || '' }}
query order_detail($order_number: String!, $contact_id: String!) {
  CRM {
    p_order(uniqueIdentifier: "order_number", uniqueIdentifierValue: $order_number) {
      _metadata { id }
      order_number
      product_name
      status
      production_stage
      subtotal
      tax
      shipping
      total
      currency
      estimated_production_start
      estimated_completion
      actual_completion_date
      shipped_at
      delivered_at
      customer_notes
      configuration_snapshot
      hs_createdate
      associations {
        contact_collection__primary(filter: { hs_object_id__eq: $contact_id }) {
          items { _metadata { id } }
        }
        p_order_status_history_collection__primary {
          items {
            status
            stage
            notes
            created_by
            hs_createdate
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Security note:** The `contact_collection` filter ensures the logged-in user actually owns this order. If the contact association is empty, the module should show "Not found."

## Steps
- [ ] Create .graphql file
- [ ] Test in GraphiQL with a known order_number
- [ ] Verify dynamic slug resolution works
- [ ] Verify status history timeline data returns correctly
- [ ] Verify contact ownership check works

